CH=(\sqrt{3}/2)AB
\angle C=30^\circ\;,\;\;|AC|=\sqrt3\, |AB|\implies
\frac{\sqrt3}2=\sin60^\circ=\sin B=\frac{|AH|}{|AB|}\implies |AH|=\frac{\sqrt3}2|AB|
\frac{\sqrt3}2=\cos30^\circ=\cos C=\frac{|CH|}{|AC|}\implies |CH|=\frac{\sqrt3}2|AC|=\frac{3}2|AB|
\Delta AHC=\Delta BAC\implies \frac{AC}{BC}=\frac{AH}{AB}=\frac{HC}{AC}\implies
CH=AC\frac{AH}{AB}
\;30-60-90\;
\;x\,:\,\sqrt3\,x\,:\,2x\;
AC=\sqrt3\,AB\;,\;\;AH=\frac{\sqrt3}2AB\implies CH=\frac32AB
